Pull-Ups Training.name: Standard Pull-Up
Pull-Ups Training.description: Grip the bar with palms facing away and pull your chin over the bar.

Pull-Ups Training.name: Chin-Up
Pull-Ups Training.description: Grip the bar with palms facing toward you and pull up.

Pull-Ups Training.name: Wide-Grip Pull-Up
Pull-Ups Training.description: Perform a pull-up with a wider-than-shoulder grip for more lat activation.

Pull-Ups Training.name: Close-Grip Pull-Up
Pull-Ups Training.description: Perform a pull-up with hands close together for more biceps engagement.

Pull-Ups Training.name: Archer Pull-Up
Pull-Ups Training.description: Pull more with one arm while extending the other outward.

Pull-Ups Training.name: Commando Pull-Up
Pull-Ups Training.description: Grip the bar with hands facing each other and pull your head to one side.

Pull-Ups Training.name: Explosive Pull-Up
Pull-Ups Training.description: Pull yourself up quickly and explosively, optionally releasing the bar briefly.

Pull-Ups Training.name: L-Sit Pull-Up
Pull-Ups Training.description: Perform a pull-up while keeping your legs extended at a 90-degree angle.

Pull-Ups Training.name: Typewriter Pull-Up
Pull-Ups Training.description: Pull yourself up and shift side to side at the top.

Pull-Ups Training.name: One-Arm Assisted Pull-Up
Pull-Ups Training.description: Use one arm more than the other to work toward a full one-arm pull-up.

Pull-Ups Training.name: One-Arm Pull-Up
Pull-Ups Training.description: Perform a pull-up using only one arm for advanced strength training.

Pull-Ups Training.name: Negative Pull-Up
Pull-Ups Training.description: Jump to the top position and slowly lower yourself for eccentric strength.

Pull-Ups Training.name: Behind-the-Neck Pull-Up
Pull-Ups Training.description: Pull up with the bar behind your head, emphasizing shoulder mobility.

Pull-Ups Training.name: Towel Pull-Up
Pull-Ups Training.description: Grip a towel over the bar for added grip strength work.

Pull-Ups Training.name: Front Lever Pull-Up
Pull-Ups Training.description: Perform a pull-up while keeping your body horizontal.

Pull-Ups Training.name: Jumping Pull-Up
Pull-Ups Training.description: Use a jump to assist the pull-up, helping build strength.

Pull-Ups Training.name: Isometric Hold Pull-Up
Pull-Ups Training.description: Hold the top or middle position of a pull-up for time.

Pull-Ups Training.name: Superman Pull-Up
Pull-Ups Training.description: Pull explosively and extend your body forward at the top.

Pull-Ups Training.name: Wall Pull
Pull-Ups Training.description: Lie on the floor under a sturdy table or bar and pull your chest up.

Pull-Ups Training.name: Inverted Rows
Pull-Ups Training.description: Hold onto a low bar or table and pull your chest towards it while keeping your body straight.

Pull-Ups Training.name: Table Rows
Pull-Ups Training.description: Lie under a sturdy table and pull your chest up towards it.

Pull-Ups Training.name: Bridge Pull
Pull-Ups Training.description: Lie on the ground, lift your hips, and pull yourself forward using your arms.

Pull-Ups Training.name: Superman Back Extension
Pull-Ups Training.description: Lie on your stomach and lift your arms and legs off the ground.

Pull-Ups Training.name: Hollow Body Pull Simulation
Pull-Ups Training.description: Lie on the ground in a hollow body position and pull your arms down as if mimicking a pull-up motion.
